## ⚙️ Technical Architecture

- Backend: Python / Flask
- Frontend: HTML / CSS / JavaScript
- Cluster: Telnet DX Cluster
- Analysis: dedicated Python scripts
- Storage: memory + local JSON files

No cloud dependency.

---

## 🗂️ Version History

### v7.3 - bug fix in analysis.html

### v7.2 — Satellite Tracker

- New **Satellite Tracker** page: real-time tracking of amateur satellites (AO-73, AO-91, ISS, RS-44, SO-50, FO-29, PO-101…)
- Positions computed locally via **sgp4** from AMSAT TLE data
- **Leaflet** map with per-satellite coverage footprint
- Elevation / azimuth / altitude table updated in real time
- **Next passes** panel (24h UTC): AOS, TCA, LOS, duration, max elevation
- Independent multi-satellite selection for pass display
- Manual keps update from CelesTrak
- AMSAT catalogue management: add/remove tracked satellites

### v7.1

**LoTW — DXCC Opportunities**

- Automatic cross-reference of the LoTW log with upcoming DX expeditions (21-day horizon)
- **🎯 DXCC OPPORTUNITIES — 21 DAYS** section in the LoTW panel, sorted by priority:
  - 🔴 NEW DXCC — country never worked
  - 🟡 UNCONFIRMED — worked but no LoTW QSL yet
  - 🔵 MISSING BAND — confirmed but some bands still to complete
- J-X countdown before each expedition ends
- Automatic date extraction from briefing text

**Briefing page fully rebuilt**

- Single unified layout for all sources (no more three redundant sections)
- **Drag & drop panels**: freely reorganizable, order saved in localStorage
- NG3K parser rewritten for structured plain-text format — expired expeditions filtered automatically
- Structured title: `Callsign · DXCC · → end date`
- Callsigns highlighted in cyan throughout summaries
- Relative timestamps (2 hours ago, 3 days ago…)
- Fixed `datetime.utcnow()` deprecation warning (Python 3.12)

### v7.0 — LoTW Integration & Bandmap Improvements

**LoTW (Logbook of the World) Integration**

- Secure login from the web interface — credentials never stored on disk
- Full log import: all uploaded QSOs + confirmed QSLs
- DXCC resolution via `cty.dat` (no dependency on optional ADIF field)
- Statistics: total QSOs, confirmed QSLs, confirmed DXCC per band (visual bar chart)
- **In HF and VHF spot tables**: red background + NEW badge = DXCC never worked / green + ✓ = already confirmed
- **★ NEW DXCC button** in HF and VHF panels to filter new DXCC only
- **In the watchlist**: NEW DXCC or ✓ LoTW badge on each callsign
- Loading spinner during synchronization (30–60s for a large log)

**Bandmap**

- Zoom increased to 100× for busy bands (e.g. 20m)
- Pin label color by mode: CW (green), SSB (blue), FT8 (purple), FT4 (pink), FT2 (mauve), RTTY (orange), PSK31 (yellow), JT65 (cyan)
- Mode legend displayed in the controls bar
- Frequency axis: only real amateur radio band edges shown
- Mouse pan (click + drag) available even at zoom 1×
- All settings persisted via localStorage

### v6.9

- VOACAP panel: local HF propagation prediction (no cloud dependency)
- Endpoint `/api/voacap?zone=EU` — MUF/LUF/REL calculation from SFI and Kp
- Zones: EU / NA / SA / AS / OC / AF
- Colored grid of bands × UTC hours, VOACAP style
- Preferred zone saved in localStorage

### v6.8

- Color palette for the bandmap background (8 themes, persisted)
- Zoom up to 100× on the bandmap
- Pin colors based on spotted mode

### v6.7

- GitHub update check reduced to once every 24 hours (anti rate-limiting)
- WL button to show only watchlist stations in the bandmap
- HF / VHF 2m / UHF 70cm / QO-100 group filters in the bandmap
- Fixed display bug on the Analysis page

### v6.6

- Bandmap: zoom and SPD density sliders
- Auto-recentering on the selected callsign

### v6.5

- Replaced `telnetlib` with `Telnetlib3` (suggestion by F5UGQ)
- Optional AI Vocal Brief button in the Solar Indices panel (Perplexity API, ~€0.01/call)

### v6.4

- Bandmap added to the home page with band and mode filtering

### v6.3

- Frequency-based sorting in HF and VHF DX panels
- Update notification banner

### v6.2

- Optional callsign addition to the watchlist from the dashboard
- FT2 mode support

### v6.1

- New DXpedition Briefing page
- Updated maps on the Index page

### v6.0 — Stable Release

